	<h2 ><a name="Workflow"></a>Workflow</h2>
	<p >
		The following localization Workflow has been designed. It's an important concept to keep in mind when using the portal to understand the HO Status Naming.
	</p>
	<p >
		<img src="<?php echo $this->baseUrl('/images/documents/Doc_FMS_Portal_Status_WF.JPG');?>" height="348" hspace="0" width="940" border="0">
	</p>
	<p >
		<span class="bold_text">HO - Ready To Loc :</span> Client created a Source String in the portal, HO has been sent to Jonckers Project Manager.
	</p>
	<p>
		<span class="bold_text">HO - Received :</span> Jonckers PM confirmed reception of the HO. Translators receive a notification email with instruction to localize the string.
	</p>
	<p>
		<span class="bold_text">HB - Completed :</span> Jonckers PM confirmed all strings are localized and have been handed back to the client.
	</p>
	<p>
		<span class="bold_text">HO - Closed:</span> Client confirmed reception of the localized strings and closed the HO.
	</p>
