	</p>
	<p>
		<span class="bold_text">Source String</span>: Enter the Source String to be sent out to localization. 
	</p>
	<p>
		<span class="bold_text">Handoff Date</span>: This date is automatically set by the System.
	</p>
	<p>
		<span class="bold_text">Handoff Source LanguageID</span>: Select ONE source language.
	</p>
	<p>
		<span class="bold_text">Handoff List Target LanguageID</span>: Select one or multiple target languages.
	</p>
		In case you are missing languages, Please contact your Jonckers PM, it can be easily added.
	</p>
	<p>
		<span class="bold_text">Handoff Instruction</span>: Write any Comment or Instructions for your Handoff that you want to pass on to Jonckers Team. This text will be included in the Notification Email. This area is rich text format enabled and allows you to add any kind of formatted text, such as hyperlinks.
	</p>
	<p>
		<span class="bold_text">Send to Jonckers</span>: This button saves the Handoff information and send it to Jonckers. The Handoff status is now set as "HO - ReadyToLoc".  
		<img src="<?php echo $this->baseUrl('/images/documents/HoStatus_readyToloc.JPG');?>" height="51" hspace="0" width="120" border="0">. It also informs Jonckers Team via email that your String is ready to be localized. 
	</p>
	
	<p>
		Notes:
	</p>
	<p>
		In case the Source String has already been submitted in a previous HO, Bento will reject your request with an error message. 
	</p>
